[metadata]
name = "Axiom.jl-intentfile"
project = "Axiom.jl"
schema_version = "1.0"

@abstract:
North-star for Axiom.jl: Provably Correct Machine Learning — a Julia-native
ML framework where shape errors, invariant violations, and model-integrity
failures are caught at compile time or through first-class verification
workflows, not in production.
@end

## Purpose

Axiom.jl is a next-generation ML framework for Julia that provides:
- Compile-time shape verification (Dense/Conv layer mismatches caught before runtime)
- Formal verification workflows via the @axiom and @ensure macros
- Coprocessor acceleration (Zig compute layer; TPU/NPU/DSP/FPGA/GPU extension paths)
- Serving APIs (REST, GraphQL, gRPC) with binary-wire gRPC support
- Model interoperability (PyTorch import / ONNX export)
- A `packages/SMTLib.jl` subpackage for SMT-backed proof obligations

The Zig compute layer (`zig/`) provides hand-optimised SIMD kernels;
`src/Abi/` carries the Idris2 ABI interface definitions. The formal-
verification surface is backed by the `src/verification/` module and
the `ResourceTracking.agda` formal spec.

## Anti-Purpose

Axiom.jl is NOT:
- A general-purpose ML framework competing on raw throughput alone
- A Python replacement (Julia is the primary language; PyCall interop is a bridge)
- A proof assistant (formal artefacts back the framework; they are not the product)
- A Rust/Go project (Zig is the low-level substrate; Julia is the user surface)

## If In Doubt

Sensitive areas — ask before changing: `src/verification/`, `src/Abi/`,
`zig/`, `packages/SMTLib.jl`, `.github/workflows/`, `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

## Committed Next-Actions

### smt-lib-subpackage-completion
- description: SMTLib.jl subpackage reaches v1.0 with full solver integration
- probe: test -f packages/SMTLib.jl/Project.toml
- status: in_progress

### zig-kernel-coverage
- description: all Zig kernels (matmul, conv, attention, pool, norm) pass parity tests
- probe: test -f test/ci/backend_parity.jl
- status: in_progress
- notes: backend_parity.jl CI test guards this surface

### idris2-abi-formal-spec
- description: src/Abi/ Idris2 ABI definitions have accompanying formal proofs
- probe: ls src/Abi/*.idr 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q .
- status: in_progress

